commitResults.messageBody: docs: Update AboutUs.md

Update Gradle from '7.6.2' to '9.1.0'.

Update Gradle libraries and plugins to:

- checkstyle = '12.0.1'
- guava = '33.5.0-jre'
- jetbrains-annotations = '26.0.2-1'
- junit-jupiter = '6.0.0'
- junit-platform-launcher = '6.0.0'
- shadow = '9.2.2'

Update package name to 'arpa.home.nustudy' from 'seedu.nustudy', because
the old package name does not make sense ('seedu' is from [the SE-EDU
project](https://se-education.org)). 'arpa.home' is chosen as the prefix
package name, because it is convention to [use our reversed Internet
domain name to begin our package
names](https://dev.java/learn/packages/#naming), but since we do not
have one, we can use the [special-use domain
'home.arpa'](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8375) instead.

Rename 'NUStudy.java' to 'App.java' as generated by the Gradle 'init'
task.

Add '.idea' folder to work with the same project settings across
different instances of IntelliJ IDEA. Only project setting files are
included.

commitResults.messageTitle: style: fix screw-up when renaming package name
commitResults.messageBody:
In the commit 9f7f3d78697f3f5a2b6d183ec20c37f93d989888, when refactoring
the package name to 'arpa.home.nustudy', the code styles got all messed
up in the process, causing the pull request checks to fail at the
':checkstyleMain' and ':checkstyleTest' tasks. This commit styles all
the code in 'src' to follow the coding style guidelines, to avoid
failing at the above tasks again.

Remove the 'misc.xml' file in the '.idea' directory, since not everyone
is using the same JDK distribution. The 'misc.xml' file seems to track
per-user editor layout configurations as well.

Add '.idea/misc.xml' to '.gitignore'.

Rearrange '.gitignore' to not ignore 'gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar'
file. It was previously incorrectly ignored because in the '.gitignore'
file, the Java section came after the Gradle section, and the Java
section ignored '*.jar', overriding the Gradle section.

The `quit` command did not work originally, because the associated logic
was accidentally deleted in 09ff5afb2f6edb329ed1359ea4c26b0fedfd6e67.
This commit resolves the issue by restoring the quit logic.
